cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this benchmark harness or its results, please cite it as below."
title: "DGX Spark Coding-Model Benchmark: a systems + methodology case study of local coding-agent evaluation"
abstract: >-
  A three-layer benchmark (SWE-bench Verified agentic repair, a TaskFlow app-build
  acceptance rubric, and LiveCodeBench single-shot code generation) evaluating three
  MoE coding models (gpt-oss-120b, Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B, NVIDIA Nemotron-3-Super-120B-A12B)
  served locally on a single NVIDIA DGX Spark (GB10). The contribution is the serving-
  feasibility matrix, failure taxonomy, and measurement pitfalls of local coding-agent
  evaluation, not a clean model ranking.
type: software
authors:
